Decomposition of Multiplicative time-series data and ARIMA forecast graph for 2019-nCoV prevalence. From top to bottom, the lines represent actual observations, the trend, seasonal, and random components

To assess the efficacy of the two prediction methods used in this study, contrasts between the raw series observed and the predicted values obtained through the two methods were compared. The mean absolute error (MAE) and Root mean square error (RMSE) have been chosen as measurements, since the combined and chosen estimates for calculating bias and model accuracy as analytical methods have been used widely (Christodoulos et al. 2011):\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
